text: Aleksi Leppä (born 2 September 1994) is a Finnish sport shooter. He participated at the 2018 ISSF World Shooting Championships, winning two gold medals.300m STANDARD RIFLE MEN300m RIFLE 3 POSITIONS MEN Leppä's coach is his father, Marko Leppä. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:Living people Category:1994 births Category:Finnish male sport shooters Category:ISSF rifle shooters Category:People from Hamina
